  "text": "Apart from cTnT, XBs also have a major effect on cardiac thin filaments through cooperative mechanisms, a process in which the strongly bound XBs promote the recruitment of other strong XBs by affecting the movement of tropomyosin (Tm) on the actin filament [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Because of their major effects on thin filament activation, differences in the expression Correspondence to Murali Chandra: m u r a l i @ v e t m e d . w s u . e d u Abbreviations used in this paper: cTnT, cardiac troponin T; MHC, myosin heavy chain; ML, muscle length; NLRD, nonlinear recruitment distortion; PTU, propylthiouracil; RcTnT, rat cTnT; RU, regulatory unit; SL, sarcomere length; Tm, tropomyosin; Tn, troponin; XB, cross-bridge.",
